cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper deals with the sensitivity of Deep Convolutional Networks (DCNs) to input-agnostic perturbations, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the causes and implications of this behavior, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper includes visual patterns and noise, which could be related to multimedia (cs.MM).
